.TH GAT-GO 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-go \- print or switch to an existing worktree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat go
.I <ticket|^|@>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Looks up a worktree by branch name, path basename, full path, or a shortcut
.RI ( ^
for the default branch's worktree,
.I @
for the current worktree), records an access timestamp, and reports the path.
With shell integration active it changes the current directory; otherwise it
prints the path. Unlike
.BR gat\-new (1),
it does not create a worktree unless
.B \-\-create
is given.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-create
Create the worktree if it does not exist.
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " prefix"
Prefix for numeric ticket targets.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-prefix
Do not prefix a numeric target.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json|shell"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat go 12345
gat go ^
gat go 12345 \-\-create
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-path (1),
.BR gat\-switch (1)
